App Store Description
Short Description (for search results):
Document on-call triage encounters quickly and securely. AI-powered parsing, fully offline, HIPAA-conscious design.
Full Description:
OnCall Scribe helps physicians document patient triage encounters during on-call shifts — quickly, securely, and entirely on-device.
THE PROBLEM
On-call doctors receive triage messages from answering services as poorly formatted text blobs. These messages have inconsistent spacing, abbreviations, and missing delimiters. Documenting each encounter means manually extracting patient details while half-asleep at 2 AM, with no good way to search your history or generate handoff reports.
THE SOLUTION
Copy the triage message, paste it into OnCall Scribe, and let on-device AI parse it into structured fields: patient name, callback number, date of birth, attending physician, and chief complaint. Add your clinical advice and disposition, then save. That's it — 30 seconds per encounter.
KEY FEATURES

AI-Powered Parsing — Uses Apple's on-device Foundation Models to intelligently extract patient data from messy answering service messages. No internet required.
Specialty Customization — Configure for your specialty (OB/GYN, Pediatrics, Cardiology, Psychiatry, Family Medicine, and more). The app adapts terminology, disposition options, and parsing rules to match your practice.
Search Everything — Full-text search across all records. Find any patient, any complaint, any date instantly.
Shift Handoff Export — Generate formatted triage logs for any date range and share via email, text, or any app. Perfect for end-of-shift handoffs.
100% Offline — No account required. No cloud sync. No data ever leaves your device. Works in airplane mode.
Privacy by Design — All data stored locally with iOS encryption. No analytics, no tracking, no third-party SDKs. Your patient data stays on your phone.

DESIGNED FOR REAL ON-CALL USE

Dark mode optimized for nighttime use
Large tap targets for one-handed operation
Quick-entry priority levels (Routine / Urgent / Emergent)
Callback button to dial patients directly
Follow-up flags so nothing falls through the cracks

WHO IT'S FOR
OnCall Scribe is designed for physicians, nurse practitioners, and physician assistants who take call and receive patient triage messages via text or pager. It's a documentation tool for healthcare professionals — not a patient-facing app.
REQUIREMENTS

iPhone 15 Pro or newer (Apple Intelligence required for AI parsing)
iOS 26 or later
Apple Intelligence must be enabled in Settings


