Privacy Policy
OnCall Scribe Privacy Policy
Last Updated: February 5, 2026
Summary
OnCall Scribe does not collect, store, transmit, or share any personal data or patient health information. All data you enter into the app remains exclusively on your device.
Data Storage
All triage records, settings, and preferences are stored locally on your iPhone using Apple's SwiftData framework. Data is encrypted at rest using iOS file protection (NSFileProtectionComplete), meaning it is encrypted whenever your device is locked.
No data is stored on external servers, cloud services, or any third-party infrastructure.
Data Collection
OnCall Scribe collects no data whatsoever. Specifically:

No analytics — We do not track how you use the app
No crash reporting — We do not collect crash logs
No advertising — There are no ads and no ad tracking
No third-party SDKs — The app contains no Facebook, Google, Firebase, or other third-party code
No network calls — The app makes zero internet connections and functions fully offline

AI Processing
OnCall Scribe uses Apple's Foundation Models framework to parse triage messages. This AI processing happens entirely on your device using Apple's on-device language model. No text is sent to Apple, Anthropic, OpenAI, or any other external service for processing.
Data Sharing
When you use the Export feature to share triage records (via email, text message, or other apps), you are explicitly choosing to share that data. OnCall Scribe does not automatically share any data — all sharing is user-initiated.
Data Retention
Your data remains on your device until you delete it. You can delete individual records within the app, or delete all data by uninstalling the app.
HIPAA Compliance
OnCall Scribe is designed with healthcare privacy in mind. Because all data is stored locally and no data is transmitted to any third party, there is no Business Associate Agreement (BAA) required. However, you are responsible for ensuring your use of the app and any exported records complies with your institution's HIPAA policies and procedures.
Children's Privacy
OnCall Scribe is designed for healthcare professionals and is not intended for use by children under 18.
Changes to This Policy
If we update this privacy policy, we will post the new version at this URL and update the "Last Updated" date.
Contact
If you have questions about this privacy policy, contact:
