Support Page Content
OnCall Scribe Support
Frequently Asked Questions
Q: Why isn't AI parsing working?
A: AI parsing requires an iPhone 15 Pro or newer with Apple Intelligence enabled. Go to Settings → Apple Intelligence & Siri and make sure Apple Intelligence is turned on. The app will use basic pattern matching as a fallback on unsupported devices.
Q: Where is my data stored?
A: All data is stored locally on your iPhone. Nothing is uploaded to the cloud or any external server.
Q: Can I sync between devices?
A: Not currently. To maintain privacy and avoid HIPAA concerns, OnCall Scribe does not include cloud sync. You can export records and transfer them manually if needed.
Q: How do I export my records?
A: Tap the share icon on the main screen, select a date range, and tap Share. You can send the formatted triage log via email, text, AirDrop, or any other sharing method.
Q: I accidentally deleted a record. Can I recover it?
A: Unfortunately, deleted records cannot be recovered. We recommend exporting important records before deleting them.
Q: How do I change my specialty?
A: Go to Settings (gear icon) and tap on Specialty to select a different medical specialty.
Q: Does this app replace my EMR documentation?
A: No. OnCall Scribe is a personal documentation tool to help you track triage encounters during on-call shifts. You should still complete all required documentation in your institution's official medical record system.
